{"article_id":"bSPbhpOGaAST7gTk","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Former Vice President Joe Biden decisively won the South Carolina Democratic primary on Saturday ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"claiming his first victory of the 2020 race","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"and giving a crucial boost to his struggling campaign ahead of Super Tuesday .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"The victory tracked","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"with polls indicating","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"that Biden ,","depth":12},{"id":6,"text":"buoyed by support among black voters ,","depth":12},{"id":7,"text":"had a significant lead in the state for months over Sen. Bernie Sanders and others ,","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"despite the surging Vermont senator beginning to close the gap after early primary wins","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"that rocketed him to front-runner status .","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"Fox News projects","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"Sanders will finish second ,","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"followed by wealthy progressive activist Tom Steyer","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"-- who ended his campaign within hours of polls closing .","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"Biden had banked on his `` firewall '' of South Carolina","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"to essentially save his flagging presidential bid .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"As the former primary front-runner took the stage at his victory party in Columbia , S.C. ,","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"he hugged South Carolina Rep. Jim Clyburn","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"and thanked him for his recent endorsement","depth":13},{"id":19,"text":"saying ,","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"`` You brought me back . ''","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"\" Just days ago the press and the pundits had declared this candidacy dead .","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"Now","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"thanks to all of you , the heart of the Democratic Party , we just won","depth":14},{"id":24,"text":"and we won big","depth":15},{"id":25,"text":"because of you , \"","depth":15},{"id":26,"text":"Biden declared .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"`` This is the moment","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"to choose the path forward for our party ,","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"this is the moment","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"and it 's arrived ,","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"maybe sooner","depth":14},{"id":32,"text":"than anyone guessed","depth":15},{"id":33,"text":"it would","depth":15},{"id":34,"text":"but it 's here , ''","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"Biden told supporters in Columbia .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Biden will close in on Sanders ' delegate lead","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"coming out of South Carolina ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"though Sanders may still be well-positioned in a number of delegate-rich Super Tuesday states .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"A total of 54 pledged delegates were at stake Saturday .","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"With 87 percent of returns in , Biden had 48.8 percent ,","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"Sanders had 19.8 percent","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"and Steyer had 11.5 percent .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"Behind Steyer were former South Bend Mayor Pete Buttigieg , Sen. Elizabeth Warren , D-Mass. , Sen. Amy Klobuchar , D-Minn. , and Rep. Tulsi Gabbard , D-Hawaii .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"The win could help Biden reset the race","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"after Sanders racked up victories in New Hampshire and Nevada","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"and essentially tied the Iowa caucuses with Buttigieg .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"The performance had led to speculation","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"that Sanders may soon be unstoppable on his path to the Democratic nomination ,","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"as well as questions","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"over whether Biden could resurrect his campaign","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"after the former front-runner failed to win any of the first three states on the calendar .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"But Biden ,","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"who has sought to present himself as the moderate","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"best positioned","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"to beat President Trump in November ,","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"was hoping","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"that he could get back on the board in southern states with higher numbers of black voters .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"Iowa and New Hampshire are both whiter states than the U.S. as a whole ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"while Nevada showed Sanders ' strength with Hispanic voters .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Biden took a series of veiled jabs at his left-wing rival ,","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"telling the crowd","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"that `` most Americans do n't want the promise of revolution ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"they want more than promises --","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"they want results . ''","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"`` We have the option","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"of winning big","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"or losing big ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"that 's the choice , ''","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"he said , in reference to fears about Sanders ' electability .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"Sanders , meanwhile , said","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"he had created a movement","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"and emphasized the importance","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"of bringing young people , working-class people and others into that movement","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"as he downplayed his loss in South Carolina .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"`` Our job together is to reach out to those working people","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"and say","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"we do care about you ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"join us","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"and come into our movement , ''","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"`` You can not win them all .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"Lotta ' states out there , ''","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"Sanders said","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"as he congratulated Biden .","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"`` Nobody wins them all . ''","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"A Fox News voter analysis found","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"that Biden was the highest rated by voters on who could best handle race issues .","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"He got 38 percent","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"compared with Sanders ' 19 percent .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"Black voters , in the end , overwhelmingly picked Biden on Saturday .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"Late deciders also went big for Biden ,","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"the analysis found ,","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"with 48 percent breaking for Biden ,","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"and only 15 percent going for Sanders .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"Trump used Biden 's win","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"to mock former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg ,","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"who is sitting out the early contests","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"but spending astonishing sums on ads in a bid","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"to dominate Super Tuesday .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"`` Sleepy Joe Biden ' s victory in the South Carolina Democrat Primary should be the end of Mini Mike Bloomberg ' s Joke of a campaign .","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"After the worst debate performance in the history of presidential debates , Mini Mike now has Biden split up his very few voters ,","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"taking many away ! ''","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"he tweeted .","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"The former vice president told reporters on Saturday morning","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"that he 's `` optimistic not just about today ''","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"but about `` the whole process from here on out . ''","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"And Biden predicted","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"`` the bigger the win '' in South Carolina ,","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"`` the bigger the bump '' he 'll get going into the 14 Super Tuesday states","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"that hold contests in three days .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"Biden said","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"that a strong win in South Carolina will `` put me in a position","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"to do well in North Carolina and Alabama and other states","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"that I think","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"in the Democratic primary I can do very well . ''","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"it 'll even be over after Super Tuesday .","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"I think","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"it 's so it can go on to states","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"that are ones","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"I feel very good about , ''","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"he emphasized .","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"Polls had suggested","depth":6},{"id":125,"text":"Biden should win the contest ,","depth":6},{"id":126,"text":"but some of those polls had shown a narrower lead","depth":6},{"id":127,"text":"and prompted Sanders supporters to hope","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"that he could snatch it .","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"Ahead of the primary , there was speculation","depth":6},{"id":130,"text":"that the state 's open primary system","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"--","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"under which Republicans could technically vote in the Democratic race --","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"could lead to GOP voters mischievously backing Sanders in a bid","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"to boost the candidate","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"some conservatives would rather see face Trump in November .","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"if that happened ,","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"it was n't enough","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"to cut down Biden 's advantage .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"The Sanders surge has scared party moderates ,","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"who fear","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"that the far-left candidate could hand Trump the presidency as well as Republican control of the House and Senate .","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"Sanders has sought to push back on the narrative","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"that he is unelectable ,","depth":6},{"id":145,"text":"pointing to polls","depth":7},{"id":146,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"he says","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"show him beating Trump in the fall .","depth":6},{"id":149,"text":"`` Take a look at the last 60 national polls","depth":7},{"id":150,"text":"that have been done , ''","depth":7},{"id":151,"text":"Sanders told a crowd in Columbia , South Carolina on Friday .","depth":6},{"id":152,"text":"`` Bernie beats Trump 56 out of the 60 times .","depth":6},{"id":153,"text":"Take a look at some of the polls in the battleground states like Pennsylvania , Wisconsin , Michigan","depth":7},{"id":154,"text":"-- Bernie beats Trump . \"","depth":7},{"id":155,"text":"Other candidates , such as Buttigieg and Klobuchar , are looking ahead to Super Tuesday already","depth":4},{"id":156,"text":"and keeping expectations low for Saturday","depth":4},{"id":157,"text":"-- with a Buttigieg campaign aide telling Fox News","depth":4},{"id":158,"text":"that they 're looking for a fourth- or fifth-place finish .","depth":4},{"id":159,"text":"But Steyer was hoping for a strong showing in South Carolina ,","depth":5},{"id":160,"text":"with polls placing him in third place behind Biden and Sanders","depth":5},{"id":161,"text":"as he heavily courted black voters .","depth":4},{"id":162,"text":"Steyer told Fox News on Friday","depth":5},{"id":163,"text":"how he viewed his chances .","depth":5},{"id":164,"text":"`` We have a very good team here .","depth":6},{"id":165,"text":"I ' ve spent a lot of time on the ground","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"and I ' m talking straightforwardly about issues , ''","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":168,"text":"`` This is a heavily African-American state .","depth":7},{"id":169,"text":"I talk very straightforwardly about race .","depth":7},{"id":170,"text":"I ' m the only person","depth":8},{"id":171,"text":"talking about reparations for slavery .","depth":8},{"id":172,"text":"I think","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"I ' ve been here the most","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"and looked most people in the eye","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"and talked most straightforwardly","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"and I think","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"that ' s why . \"","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":355,"left":332,"right":354,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":332,"left":301,"right":331,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":301,"left":237,"right":300,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":237,"left":180,"right":236,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":0,"right":179,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":236,"left":215,"right":235,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":190,"right":214,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":190,"left":3,"right":189,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":185,"right":188,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":4,"right":184,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":184,"left":182,"right":183,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":181,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":181,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":183,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":186,"right":187,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":186,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":187,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":211,"right":213,"relation":"e